<div id="review_42535976" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/42535976" />
    <a title="marissa  sammy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/122026-marissa-sammy"><img alt="marissa  sammy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1181243339p2/122026.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/42535976?book_show_action=true">Jan 09, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="marissa  sammy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="marissa  sammy" href="/user/show/122026-marissa-sammy">marissa  sammy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">those who talk incessantly about their love affairs to bored overly-polite friends</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to marissa  sammy by: </span>
      i read this for a class
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer42535976" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5536501723751957590">Gah -- I found this insufferably narcissistic and eye-rolling to read, devoid of any sympathetic characters save the zoo-lady Jacqueline, and incredibly unsatisfying in every way. The only reason I gave it two stars is because Winterson obviously has talent -- there were a few places where the imagery was striking enough to pierce my annoyance -- and clearly this is a matter of taste and preference. It&apos;s technically and emotionally proficient, but just doesn&apos;t resonate with me personally.</span>
  <span id="freeText5536501723751957590" style="display:none">Gah -- I found this insufferably narcissistic and eye-rolling to read, devoid of any sympathetic characters save the zoo-lady Jacqueline, and incredibly unsatisfying in every way. The only reason I gave it two stars is because Winterson obviously has talent -- there were a few places where the imagery was striking enough to pierce my annoyance -- and clearly this is a matter of taste and preference. It's technically and emotionally proficient, but just doesn't resonate with me personally.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5536501723751957590" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
